frameDefinitions: In this frame a group of Individuals intentionally come together to form a Group.

A Suspect in a Current_jurisdiction is forced by Authorities (of the Current_jurisdiction) to go to the Crime_jurisdiction, i.e. the jurisdiction which requested that the Suspect be handed over for trial for a crime which he or she is suspected to have committed in the Crime_jurisdiction.
An Authority excuses an Offense that an Offender has committed, with the effect of ending or preventing any punishment.
An Employee voluntarily leaves the service of an Employer.
An Entity is at a particular stage of its development.
A Self_mover leaves an initial Source location.
frameExamples: We <t>assembled</t> in the courtyard to talk about our future plans.
The fraud was <t>extradited</t> from Venezuela to the US.
President Ford <t>pardoned</t> her after it came to light she was being held in Japan as an 'enemy alien' and was secretly working to subvert the broadcasts DNI
Leah <t>quit</t> her job after one month because of an evil force.
The <t>Next Generation</t> Internet (NGI) Program has been successfully completed.
listRoleDefinitions: The <fen>Individuals</fen> are self-movers who intentionally assemble together.
The <fen>Group</fen> describes the resulting formation of the <fen>Individuals</fen>.

<fen>Party_1</fen> is the grammatically more prominent participant in the assembling event.  It can refer to either a single individual or a larger party separate from <fen>Party_2</fen> previous to the assembling.
A grammatically less prominent participant in the assembling event.  It can refer to either a single individual or a larger party separate from <fen>Party_1</fen> previous to the assembling.
The <fen>Time</fen> is when the assembling occurs.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the assembling occurs.
The <fen>Authorities</fen> act on behalf of the <fen>Current_jurisdiction</fen>, giving up the <fen>Suspect</fen> to the Crime_jurisdiction.
The jurisdiction (generally a nation) the <fen>Suspect</fen> starts off in.
The jurisdiction (generally a nation) to which the <fen>Suspect</fen> is sent.
The Suspect is forced to go to the jurisdiction where a crime he or she is suspected of took place or is being tried.
The time at which  the <fen>Suspect</fen> is moved.
The location where the extradition occurs.
This role denotes the offender that seeks or gets the pardon.
Authority is the organization or person taht grants the pardon.
This role denotes the the illegal act that the <fen>Offender</fen> is pardoned for.
This role denotes the time when the pardon is given
The location at which the pardoning takes place.
The person who is obligated to perform some task in order to receive compensation.
The person (or institution) in whose employ  the <fen>Employee</fen> stood.
The Field that one works in.
The label given to a particular type of service that the employer quits.
This role identifies the Time when an <fen>Employee</fen> quits the employment of the <fen>Employer</fen>.
This role identifies the place where the <fen>Employee</fen> quits the employment of the <fen>Employer</fen>.
The object that has reached a particular stage of its development.
The time at which the progress occurs.
This is the entity which moves under its own power.

Any expression which implies a definite starting-point of motion expresses the frame element <fen>Source</fen>. In prepositional phrases, the prepositional object expresses the starting point of motion. In particles, the starting point of motion is understood from context.
The time at which the motion takes place.
The <fen>Place</fen> is where the motion (which is specified by a <fen>Source</fen>, <fen>Path</fen> or <fen>Goal</fen>) is located.

<fex>In Europe</fex> they extradite more freely than in North America.
Defense minister Ivanov rules out pardon <fex>for Chechen rebel leader Maskhadov</fex>.
<fex>The governement</fex> issued a pardon to the two convicts.
They demanded a pardon to John <fex>for inadverdent manslaughter</fex>.
The families demanded a <fex>posthumous</fex> pardon for the executed soldiers.

On 1 March 2002, Andreyev was found guilty of libel and conditionally sentenced
to two years in prison and then pardoned <fex>in the courtroom</fex>.
He replaces Michael Lawrie, 50, who quit <fex>IBM</fex> to run Siebel.
Actually Iquit <fex>in the lobby</fex> before I got to my office.
We offer advice for very advanced <fex>learners of English</fex> on the different EFL/ESL exams.
